## 3. Commands — replication & health (non-Citus and general)

```sql
-- Primary: who is replicating, how far behind?
SELECT application_name, client_addr, state, sync_state,
       pg_wal_lsn_diff(pg_current_wal_lsn(), sent_lsn) AS sent_lag_bytes,
       pg_wal_lsn_diff(sent_lsn, write_lsn) AS write_lag_bytes,
       pg_wal_lsn_diff(write_lsn, flush_lsn) AS flush_lag_bytes,
       pg_wal_lsn_diff(flush_lsn, replay_lsn) AS replay_lag_bytes
FROM pg_stat_replication;

-- Standby: am I receiving WAL?
SELECT status, conninfo, received_lsn, latest_end_lsn
FROM pg_stat_wal_receiver;

-- Role
SELECT pg_is_in_recovery();  -- true = standby
```

```bash
# Patroni (example)
patronictl -c /etc/patroni.yml list
patronictl -c /etc/patroni.yml show-config
```

