## 6. DBA issues — PostgreSQL HA

| Issue | What goes wrong | What to check |
|-------|-----------------|---------------|
| **Replication lag** | Standby too slow; **failover** loses recent data if async. | `pg_stat_replication`, disk IO, `max_wal_size`, network. |
| **Split-brain** (self-managed) | Two primaries — **data corruption**. | **Patroni fencing**, **STONITH**, **quorum** in DCS; never **manual promote** without understanding. |
| **Failover flapping** | Network blip toggles leader. | **TTL**, **health checks**, **synchronous_commit** policy. |
| **Connection storms** | Apps don’t use **pooler** or **retry** on failover. | **PgBouncer** / pool mode, app **timeouts**, **JDBC** targetServerType. |
| **Disk full on primary** | WAL can’t write — **outage**. | Alerts on **volume %**, **WAL** retention, **archiving**. |

