## 7. DBA issues — Citus-specific

| Issue | What goes wrong | What to check |
|-------|-----------------|---------------|
| **Bad distribution key** | **Skew** — one worker hot, others idle. | Shard counts, **rebalancer**, query plans (`EXPLAIN`). |
| **Cross-shard joins** | Slow without **colocation** or **reference tables**. | `create_reference_table`, **colocate_with**, redesign. |
| **Distributed deadlocks** | Different order of locks across workers. | App transaction design; `citus_dist_stat_activity` (if available). |
| **DDL / metadata** | **Distributed** DDL blocks or fails mid-way. | Citus version, **MX** / **metadata** sync — follow upgrade notes. |
| **Rebalance** | Long locks, IO spike. | **Maintenance window**, **drain** traffic, monitor **progress**. |
| **Vacuum / bloat** | Per-node **autovacuum** must keep up on **every** worker. | **Per-node** stats; **large** tenants on one shard hurt. |
| **Coordinator SPOF** | If coordinator is single — **whole cluster** down for writes. | **HA design** for coordinator (product-specific). |

